    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02223.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <note type="editorial" resp="#ht" place="top">see notes 26 &amp; 28 Aug
                        '88</note>
                    <date when="1884-08-09">Aug 9. 84.</date>
                    <handShift rend="printed"/>
                    <name type="place">EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT</name>
                    <name type="place">THE CENTURY MAGAZINE</name>
                    <name type="place">UNION SQUARE NEW YORK</name>
                    <handShift rend="manuscript"/>
                    <name type="place">Marion, Mass</name>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Mr. Whitman,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> I am glad you can do the <hi rend="underline">nursing</hi> article.<ptr target="loc.02223_n1"/> Thanks for the
                Father Taylor<ptr target="loc.02223_n2"/>&#8212;should you not include Emerson in the list of his praisers which you
                give? </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                <signed>R.W. Gilder</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p> We will try to find a photograph from life. </p>
            </postscript>
